HEADWORD: Idiocy
<hw>Id"i*o*cy</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧d"⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From <ets>idiot</ets>; cf. Gr. <?/ uncouthness, lack of education,
fr. <?/. See <er>Idiot</er>, and cf. <er>Idiotcy</er>.]</ety> <def>The
condition or quality of being an idiot; absence, or marked deficiency,
of sense and intelligence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will undertake to convict a man of <qex>idiocy</qex>, if he can
not see the proof that three angles of a triangle are equal to two right
angles.</q> <rj><qau>F. W. Robertson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idiocyclophanous</ent>⟦br⟧
